text: Abdessalam Ameknassi is a Moroccan karateka. In 2018, he won one of the bronze medals in the men's kumite 60 kg event at the 2018 World Karate Championships held in Madrid, Spain. At the 2018 Mediterranean Games held in Tarragona, Spain, he won the gold medal in the men's kumite 60 kg event. In 2019, he represented Morocco at the 2019 African Games held in Rabat, Morocco and he won the silver medal in the men's kumite 60 kg event.
